<item>
            <title>[SPARK-8289] Provide a specific stack size with all Java implementations to prevent stack overflows with certain tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-8289</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Default stack sizes differ per Java implementation - so tests can pass for those with higher stack sizes (OpenJDK) but will fail with Oracle or IBM Java owing to lower default sizes. In particular we can see this happening with the JavaALSSuite - with 15 iterations, we get stackoverflow errors with Oracle and IBM Java. We don&apos;t with OpenJDK. This JIRA aims to address such an issue by providing a default specified stack size to be used for all Java distributions: 4096k specified for both SBT test args and for Maven test args (changing project/ScalaBuild.scala and pom.xml respectively). &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Anywhere whereby the Java vendor is not OpenJDK&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
